This past Friday a motorcycle rider was lucky to escape with his life after colliding with a car on the corner of Ontdekkers Road and Corlett Avenue in Gauteng. Roodepoort Record reports that the accident occurred at about 5.10pm. According to sources, the bike was travelling on Ontdekkers Road in the direction of the Westgate Shopping Centre when the car, travelling from the opposite direction, turned in front of him. The vehicle the motorcycle collided with. The rider only sustained moderate injuries and was seen walking around the accident scene. The accident will be the subject of an investigation by the relevant authorities. Caxton News Service